				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what are your thoughts?<a name="42966"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">May 28 04 2:48 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I would have no problem if somebody used a third-party program to assist with the more mind-numbing aspects of EQ, like training Track or Disarm Traps, or if somebody used a third-party program to twist, especially if they had carpal tunnel syndrome.
<br />

<br />
In fact, Sony has said that if somebody uses Macroquest to ease a disability or a health condition (particularly carpal tunnel), they have no problem with it.
<br />

<br />
I do have a problem with it if the macro-er is actively collecting plat or xp while away from the keyboard. Unattended kiting or tradeskilling, if it were commonplace, would make the game much worse for everybody - it would really undermine the &quot;massive multiplayer&quot; part of &quot;MMORPG&quot; if all those players were actually just bots running in circles.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
