				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: what are your thoughts?<a name="43736"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 2 04 1:17 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Personnaly I wouldnt really have an issue with any third party programs except for one aspect of it.
<br />
People make real money off EQ.  Items and characters are sold over the internet.  Using a trainer or 3rd party program to farm exp for a character that will be sold is taking content away from folks who might otherwise use that area or kill those monsters for pleasure.
<br />

<br />
EQ is a game, those who take away the content for business uses should be banned.
<br />

<br />
I dont have a huge personal issue with someone selling a character after they &quot;retire&quot; from the game.
<br />

<br />
I do take issue with a character in game, using content, that is not attended.  A Bard /afk in some safe spot singing to train up brass, or a ranger /afk with some gamepad refreshing track every few seconds is not TAKING ANYTHING FROM ME or anyone else, so I dont have a problem with that personally.
<br />

<br />
An unattended character in PoK macrod to sell buffs, or an unattended toon in any zone killing mobs is a different story, they are taking content from me and others.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
